<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-625-317  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 625 317.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 16 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Report says nat'l phone service to be disrupted. (threat by Legionof Doom computer hackers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara F.; McMullen, John E.; McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone systemsComputer hackersComputer crimesCommunications Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>REPORT SAYS NAT'L PHONE SERVICE TO BE DISRUPTED 11/16/90 NEW YORK, NEW YORK,U.S.A., 1990 NOV 16 (NB) -- Rumors that computer outlaws plan to disruptnational telephone service today to protest that day's sentencing of threeindividuals in Atlanta for computer activities involving BellSouth are beingtaken seriously by law enforcement officials, according to several reports.andM;Members of the Legion Of Doom may attempt to interrupt telephone servicetoday when several members of the hacker's group are due for sentencing inAtlanta.andM;Adam E. Grant, Franklin Darden, Jr.andP;  and Robert J. Riggs, plead guilty tocharges involving computer trespass between September 10, 1987 through July21, 1989.andM;An Associated Press report quotes officials spokespersons from BellSouth,ATandamp;T and NYNEX as saying that they are aware of threats and plan to tightensecurity on the 16th.andP;  Newsbytes has contacted various law enforcementagencies including the United States Secret Service and the New York StatePolice, concerning the alleged threats but has received no confirmations thatthreats were in fact received.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen, John F. McMullen andamp; John McCormick/19901116)</TEXT></DOC>